        "content": "<p>We need to document the current location of a specimen, but the Specimen resource only allows for information about the properties of a specimen's container, not it's location.<br>\nIs there a best practice of how to do that, or might a change to add a reference to Location be useful?<br>\nPing <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"191401\">@Eric Haas</span></p>",
        "id": 164887406,
        "sender_full_name": "Stefan Lang",
        "timestamp": 1557004700
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ping <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"191698\">@Riki Merrick</span>  and <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"191408\">@Lorraine Constable</span></p>",
        "id": 164889507,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Haas",
        "timestamp": 1557008170
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right now an extension but  this sounds like a tracker.   I imagine its like on Device:  <a href=\"http://build.fhir.org/device-definitions.html#Device.location\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://build.fhir.org/device-definitions.html#Device.location\">http://build.fhir.org/device-definitions.html#Device.location</a></p>",
        "id": 164889712,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Haas",
        "timestamp": 1557008559
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right, basically the same kind of use case as in Device</p>",
        "id": 164890000,
        "sender_full_name": "Stefan Lang",
        "timestamp": 1557009114
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So the proposal would be:<br>\nAdd Specimen.container.location as reference(Location) ?<br>\nOr better just Specimen.location ?</p>",
        "id": 164890106,
        "sender_full_name": "Stefan Lang",
        "timestamp": 1557009270
